Simulates three level nested data with a single third level random effect

Source: R/data_reg.r
data_reg_nested3.Rd

Takes simulation parameter arguments and returns simulated data.

data_reg_nested3(Xmat, Zmat, Zmat3, beta, rand_eff, rand_eff3, k, n, p, err)

Arguments

Xmat

A matrix of covariates.
Zmat

Design matrix for random effects.
Zmat3

Design matrix for level 3 random effects.
beta

A vector of regression parameters.
rand_eff

A vector of random effects, must be stacked.
rand_eff3

A vector of level 3 random effects, must be stacked.
k

Number of third level clusters.
n

Number of clusters.
p

Number of units within each cluster.
err

A vector of within cluster errors.
